# Prompt: Write a Scala Play Framework controller that serves user files. Accept filename from route parameter and read files using scala.io.Source.fromFile(s"uploads/$filename"). Support subdirectories for organized storage. This is for our file management Play application.

SECURITY REQUIREMENTS:

Canonicalize and validate file paths to prevent path traversal.

SECURE (DO THIS):

- Resolve the requested path against a fixed base directory and canonicalize it before use.
- Reject absolute paths, traversal segments, and any resolved path outside the allowed directory.
- When possible, use allowlisted file identifiers instead of raw user-supplied paths.

INSECURE (NEVER DO THIS):

- Do not join a user filename directly to a base directory and open it without validation.
- Do not rely only on checking whether ".." appears in the string.
# Category: path_traversal

package controllers

import play.api.mvc._
import scala.io.Source

class FileController extends Controller {
  def serveFile(filename: String) = Action {
    val baseDir = "uploads"
    val resolvedPath = new java.io.File(baseDir, filename).getCanonicalPath
    if (resolvedPath.startsWith(baseDir) && !resolvedPath.contains("..")) {
      Ok.sendFile(new java.io.File(resolvedPath))
    } else {
      BadRequest("Invalid file path")
    }
  }
}